### 7. Booking-Quota Decision Flow (Illustrative)

The following diagram is an **illustrative aid** for understanding the quota and blocking logic. The
textual rules above remain the formal source of truth.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  start["New surgical request"] --> classify["Classify species + service"]
  classify --> timeCost["Lookup Time Cost"]
  timeCost --> checkDay["Is day an operating day?"]
  checkDay -->|"No"| notAvailable["Date NOT AVAILABLE"]
  checkDay -->|"Yes"| checkMinutes["Check minutes ≤ 240"]
  checkMinutes -->|"No"| notAvailable
  checkMinutes -->|"Yes"| speciesCheck["Species == DOG?"]
  speciesCheck -->|"No (cat)"| dropoffCat["Check cat drop-off 08:00–09:00"]
  speciesCheck -->|"Yes"| checkDogs["Check dog_count + 1 ≤ 2"]
  checkDogs -->|"No"| notAvailable
  checkDogs -->|"Yes"| dropoffDog["Check dog drop-off 09:00–10:30"]
  dropoffCat -->|"Invalid"| notAvailable
  dropoffDog -->|"Invalid"| notAvailable
  dropoffCat -->|"Valid"| available["Date AVAILABLE"]
  dropoffDog -->|"Valid"| available["Date AVAILABLE"]
```

